ciscoFiberChannelTunnelMIB.name: ciscoFiberChannelTunnelMIB

revisions.description: Initial version. Only supports Fiber Channel TCP tunneling.

ciscoFiberChannelTunnelMIB.contactinfo: Postal: Cisco Systems, Inc. 170 West Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134-1706 USA Tel: +1 408 526 4000 E-mail: cs-cat6000@cisco.com
ciscoFiberChannelTunnelMIB.description: The CISCO-FC-TUNNEL-MIB is used to configure Fiber Channel (FC) tunneled by other protocols, i.e. TCP (Transmision Control Protocol) or UDP (User Datagram Protocol), and monitor the status of the tunnels. And Fiber Channel Command and Data messages can be tunneled by those protocols through the internet to extend the Fiber Channel network.

cftMaxTcpTunnels.name: cftMaxTcpTunnels
cftMaxTcpTunnels.description: Maximum number of Fiber Channel TCP tunnels that can be built per Fiber Channel interface.

cftTcpTunnelTable.name: cftTcpTunnelTable
cftTcpTunnelTable.reference: RFC 793, Transmission Control Protocol. RFC 2581, TCP Congestion Control
cftTcpTunnelTable.description: This table contains TCP tunnels' information for FC interfaces. FC can use these TCP tunnels to communicate with each other through the internet. The TCP tunnels will help to build up reliable connections between FC interfaces to exchange FC Command and Data information. This table is for configuring the TCP tunnels and monitoring the status of tunnels. And the number of entries in this table is decided by the MIB object cftMaxTcpTunnels.

cftTcpTunnelEntry.name: cftTcpTunnelEntry
cftTcpTunnelEntry.description: An entry contains the configuration and status objects of a TCP tunnel. The configuration includes the TCP connection 4-tuples, source IP, destination IP, source port , destination port, and some other TCP connection's options. The status includes the TCP connections and Tunnel's administration and operation. For each TCP tunnel, there are 2 TCP connections that will be built up in the tunneling. One is for FC Command communication and the other is for FC Data communication.

cftFiberChannelIf.name: cftFiberChannelIf
cftFiberChannelIf.description: The interface index of the FC interface with TCP tunneling capable.

cftTcpTunnelName.name: cftTcpTunnelName
cftTcpTunnelName.description: The name of the FC TCP tunnel.

cftTcpTunnelSrcIpType.name: cftTcpTunnelSrcIpType
cftTcpTunnelSrcIpType.description: The source IP address type of the FC TCP tunnel.

cftTcpTunnelSrcIp.name: cftTcpTunnelSrcIp
cftTcpTunnelSrcIp.description: The source IP address of the FC TCP tunnel. The type of the IP address is determined by the object cftTcpTunnelSrcIpType in the same entry.

cftTcpTunnelDestIpType.name: cftTcpTunnelDestIpType
cftTcpTunnelDestIpType.description: The destination IP address type of the FC TCP tunnel.

cftTcpTunnelDestIp.name: cftTcpTunnelDestIp
cftTcpTunnelDestIp.description: The destination IP address of the FC TCP tunnel. The type of the IP address is determined by the object cftTcpTunnelDestIpType in the same entry.

cftTcpTunnelCmdSrcPort.name: cftTcpTunnelCmdSrcPort
cftTcpTunnelCmdSrcPort.description: The source port of the TCP connection for FC Command communication.

cftTcpTunnelCmdDestPort.name: cftTcpTunnelCmdDestPort
cftTcpTunnelCmdDestPort.description: The destination port of the TCP connection for FC Command communication.

cftTcpTunnelDataSrcPort.name: cftTcpTunnelDataSrcPort
cftTcpTunnelDataSrcPort.description: The source port of the TCP connection for FC Data communication.

cftTcpTunnelDataDestPort.name: cftTcpTunnelDataDestPort
cftTcpTunnelDataDestPort.description: The destination port of the TCP connection for FC Data communication.

cftTcpTunnelCmdMWS.name: cftTcpTunnelCmdMWS
cftTcpTunnelCmdMWS.description: The maximum window size of the TCP connection for FC Command communication. ws32kbytes : means the window size is 32 kilo-bytes. ws128kbytes : means the window size is 128 kilo-bytes. ws256kbytes : means the window size is 256 kilo-bytes. ws512kbytes : means the window size is 512 kilo-bytes.

cftTcpTunnelDataMWS.name: cftTcpTunnelDataMWS
cftTcpTunnelDataMWS.description: The maximum window size of the TCP connection for FC Data communication. ws32kbytes : means the window size is 32 kilo-bytes. ws128kbytes : means the window size is 128 kilo-bytes. ws256kbytes : means the window size is 256 kilo-bytes. ws512kbytes : means the window size is 512 kilo-bytes.

cftTcpTunnelCmdKeepAliveTime.name: cftTcpTunnelCmdKeepAliveTime
cftTcpTunnelCmdKeepAliveTime.description: The keep alive time of the TCP connection for FC Command communication.

cftTcpTunnelDataKeepAliveTime.name: cftTcpTunnelDataKeepAliveTime
cftTcpTunnelDataKeepAliveTime.description: The keep alive time of the TCP connection for FC Data communication.

cftTcpTunnelCmdSelectiveAck.name: cftTcpTunnelCmdSelectiveAck
cftTcpTunnelCmdSelectiveAck.description: The selective acknowledge option of the TCP connection for FC Command communication.

cftTcpTunnelDataSelectiveAck.name: cftTcpTunnelDataSelectiveAck
cftTcpTunnelDataSelectiveAck.description: The selective acknowledge option of the TCP connection for FC Data communication.

cftTcpTunnelCmdConnectStatus.name: cftTcpTunnelCmdConnectStatus
cftTcpTunnelCmdConnectStatus.description: The status of the TCP connection for FC Command communication. connected(1) means the TCP connection for FC Command has been connected for communication. notConnected(2) means the TCP connection for FC Command is not successful.

cftTcpTunnelDataConnectStatus.name: cftTcpTunnelDataConnectStatus
cftTcpTunnelDataConnectStatus.description: The status of the TCP connection for FC Data communication. connected(1) means the TCP connection for FC Data has been connected for communication. notConnected(2) means the TCP connection for FC Data is not successful.

cftTcpTunnelOperStatus.name: cftTcpTunnelOperStatus
cftTcpTunnelOperStatus.description: The operational status of this TCP tunnel. up(1) means this TCP tunnel is up and active. down(2) means this TCP tunnel is not active.

cftTcpTunnelStatus.name: cftTcpTunnelStatus
cftTcpTunnelStatus.description: The status of this TCP tunnel entry. If this object is active, the other objects in the same row cannot be modified by the management station.

cftTcpTunnelStatsTable.name: cftTcpTunnelStatsTable
cftTcpTunnelStatsTable.description: The table of traffic statistics information for FC tunnels. The entries in this table are shown only if the cftTcpTunnelStatus object of the corresponding entries are active in the cftTcpTunnelTable.

cftTcpTunnelStatsEntry.name: cftTcpTunnelStatsEntry
cftTcpTunnelStatsEntry.description: The entry is indexed by the same index in the cftTcpTunnelTable. And this entry contains statistics information of FC Command TCP connection and FC Data TCP connection.

cftTcpTunnelCmdRxSegmentOctets.name: cftTcpTunnelCmdRxSegmentOctets
cftTcpTunnelCmdRxSegmentOctets.description: Number of TCP segment bytes received in the FC TCP Command connection.

cftTcpTunnelDataRxSegmentOctets.name: cftTcpTunnelDataRxSegmentOctets
cftTcpTunnelDataRxSegmentOctets.description: Number of TCP segment bytes received in the FC TCP Data connection.

cftTcpTunnelCmdRxPrestufOctets.name: cftTcpTunnelCmdRxPrestufOctets
cftTcpTunnelCmdRxPrestufOctets.description: Number of bytes received before stuffing the internal hardware bus header in the FC TCP Command connection.

cftTcpTunnelDataRxPrestufOctets.name: cftTcpTunnelDataRxPrestufOctets
cftTcpTunnelDataRxPrestufOctets.description: Number of bytes received before stuffing the internal hardware bus header in the FC TCP Data connection.

cftTcpTunnelCmdRxPoststufOctets.name: cftTcpTunnelCmdRxPoststufOctets
cftTcpTunnelCmdRxPoststufOctets.description: Number of bytes received after stuffing the internal hardward bus header in the FC TCP Command connection.

cftTcpTunnelDataRxPoststufOctets.name: cftTcpTunnelDataRxPoststufOctets
cftTcpTunnelDataRxPoststufOctets.description: Number of bytes received after stuffing the internal hardward bus header in the FC TCP Data connection.

cftTcpTunnelCmdTxOctets.name: cftTcpTunnelCmdTxOctets
cftTcpTunnelCmdTxOctets.description: Number of bytes sent in the FC TCP Command connection.

cftTcpTunnelDataTxOctets.name: cftTcpTunnelDataTxOctets
cftTcpTunnelDataTxOctets.description: Number of bytes sent in the FC TCP Data connection.

cftTcpTunnelCmdTxPkts.name: cftTcpTunnelCmdTxPkts
cftTcpTunnelCmdTxPkts.description: Number of packets sent in the FC TCP Command connection.

cftTcpTunnelDataTxPkts.name: cftTcpTunnelDataTxPkts
cftTcpTunnelDataTxPkts.description: Number of packets sent in the FC TCP Data connection.

cftTcpTunnelCmdTxDrops.name: cftTcpTunnelCmdTxDrops
cftTcpTunnelCmdTxDrops.description: Number of packets dropped in the FC TCP Command connection.

cftTcpTunnelDataTxDrops.name: cftTcpTunnelDataTxDrops
cftTcpTunnelDataTxDrops.description: Number of packets dropped in the FC TCP Data connection.

cftIfTcpTable.name: cftIfTcpTable
cftIfTcpTable.description: This table contains the statistics information of the Fiber Channel interface with the ability of TCP tunneling.

cftIfTcpEntry.name: cftIfTcpEntry
cftIfTcpEntry.description: This entry contains TCP statistics information for a given FC interface with the ability of TCP tunneling.

cftIfTcpIndex.name: cftIfTcpIndex
cftIfTcpIndex.description: The interface index of the FC interface capable of carrying TCP tunnels.

cftIfTcpConnAccepted.name: cftIfTcpConnAccepted
cftIfTcpConnAccepted.description: Number of TCP requested connections accepted.

cftIfTcpConnClosed.name: cftIfTcpConnClosed
cftIfTcpConnClosed.description: Number of TCP connections closed. This includes those connections dropped.

cftIfTcpTxPkts.name: cftIfTcpTxPkts
cftIfTcpTxPkts.description: Number of TCP transmitting packets. This includes TCP control and data packets.

cftIfTcpTxDataPkts.name: cftIfTcpTxDataPkts
cftIfTcpTxDataPkts.description: Number of TCP transmitting data packets. This doesn't include those TCP control traffic.

cftIfTcpTxDataOctets.name: cftIfTcpTxDataOctets
cftIfTcpTxDataOctets.description: Number of TCP transmitting data octets. This doesn't include those TCP control traffic.

cftIfTcpRetxDataPkts.name: cftIfTcpRetxDataPkts
cftIfTcpRetxDataPkts.description: Number of TCP re-transmitting data packets. This doesn't include those TCP control traffic.

cftIfTcpRetxDataOctets.name: cftIfTcpRetxDataOctets
cftIfTcpRetxDataOctets.description: Number of TCP re-transmitting data octets. This doesn't include those TCP control traffic.

cftIfTcpRxInSequencePkts.name: cftIfTcpRxInSequencePkts
cftIfTcpRxInSequencePkts.description: Number of TCP packets received in sequence.

cftIfTcpRxInSequenceOctets.name: cftIfTcpRxInSequenceOctets
cftIfTcpRxInSequenceOctets.description: Number of TCP octets received in sequence.

cftIfTcpRxCcksumErrPkts.name: cftIfTcpRxCcksumErrPkts
cftIfTcpRxCcksumErrPkts.description: Number of TCP packets received with checksum error.

cftIfTcpRxBadOffsetPkts.name: cftIfTcpRxBadOffsetPkts
cftIfTcpRxBadOffsetPkts.description: Number of TCP packets received with bad offset.

cftIfTcpRxOutOfOrderPkts.name: cftIfTcpRxOutOfOrderPkts
cftIfTcpRxOutOfOrderPkts.description: Number of out-of-order TCP packets received.

cftIfTcpRxOutOfOrderOctets.name: cftIfTcpRxOutOfOrderOctets
cftIfTcpRxOutOfOrderOctets.description: Number of out-of-order TCP octets received.

cftIfTcpExtTable.name: cftIfTcpExtTable
cftIfTcpExtTable.reference: RFC 793, Transmission Control Protocol. RFC 2581, TCP Congestion Control
cftIfTcpExtTable.description: This table contains the statistics information of the Fiber Channel interface with the ability of TCP tunneling. This table is an extension of cftIfTcpTable and this table provides more specific counters that not all TCP protocol stack will support.

cftIfTcpExtEntry.name: cftIfTcpExtEntry
cftIfTcpExtEntry.description: This entry contains TCP statistics information for a given FC interface with the ability of TCP tunneling.

cftIfTcpEmbryonicConnDrops.name: cftIfTcpEmbryonicConnDrops
cftIfTcpEmbryonicConnDrops.description: Number of TCP embryonic connections dropped. The embryonic drop counter tells the user how many times the connections did not go through because of not receiving a reply for the SYN packets - which gives a measure for the quality of the path between the two peers.

cftIfTcpSegsTryToGetRTT.name: cftIfTcpSegsTryToGetRTT
cftIfTcpSegsTryToGetRTT.description: Number of TCP segments which try to get RTT (Round Trip Time).

cftIfTcpSegsSucceedToGetRTT.name: cftIfTcpSegsSucceedToGetRTT
cftIfTcpSegsSucceedToGetRTT.description: Number of TCP segments which get RTT (Round Trip Time) successfully.

cftIfTcpDelayedAcksSent.name: cftIfTcpDelayedAcksSent
cftIfTcpDelayedAcksSent.reference: RFC 1072, TCP Extensions for Long-Delay Paths, Section 4.2 (A)
cftIfTcpDelayedAcksSent.description: number of TCP delayed ACKs sent.

cftIfTcpConnDroppedRxTimeout.name: cftIfTcpConnDroppedRxTimeout
cftIfTcpConnDroppedRxTimeout.description: Number of TCP connections dropped because of receiving timeout.

cftIfTcpKeepaliveProbesSent.name: cftIfTcpKeepaliveProbesSent
cftIfTcpKeepaliveProbesSent.description: Number of TCP keep-alive probes sent.

cftIfTcpConnDroppedInKeepalive.name: cftIfTcpConnDroppedInKeepalive
cftIfTcpConnDroppedInKeepalive.description: Number of TCP connections dropped in keepalive.

cftIfTcpConnDroppedInPersist.name: cftIfTcpConnDroppedInPersist
cftIfTcpConnDroppedInPersist.description: Number of TCP connections dropped in persisting.

cftIfTcpConnDrainedByNoMemory.name: cftIfTcpConnDrainedByNoMemory
cftIfTcpConnDrainedByNoMemory.description: Number of TCP connections drained dut to memory shortage.

cftIfTcpAckOnlyPkts.name: cftIfTcpAckOnlyPkts
cftIfTcpAckOnlyPkts.description: Number of TCP packets sent with only ACK flag on.

cftIfTcpTxWindowProbes.name: cftIfTcpTxWindowProbes
cftIfTcpTxWindowProbes.description: Number of TCP window probing packets sent.

cftIfTcpTxURGPkts.name: cftIfTcpTxURGPkts
cftIfTcpTxURGPkts.description: Number of TCP packets sent with URG flag on.

cftIfTcpTxWindowUpdateOnlyPkts.name: cftIfTcpTxWindowUpdateOnlyPkts
cftIfTcpTxWindowUpdateOnlyPkts.description: Number of TCP packets sent only for only updating the window size.

cftIfTcpTxControlPkts.name: cftIfTcpTxControlPkts
cftIfTcpTxControlPkts.description: Number of TCP packets sent with SYN, FIN, or RST flags on.

cftIfTcpRxDroppedByNoMemory.name: cftIfTcpRxDroppedByNoMemory
cftIfTcpRxDroppedByNoMemory.description: Number of receiving TCP packets dropped because of lacking of memory.

cftIfTcpRxTooShort.name: cftIfTcpRxTooShort
cftIfTcpRxTooShort.description: Number of TCP packets received with too short length.

cftIfTcpRxDupOnlyPkts.name: cftIfTcpRxDupOnlyPkts
cftIfTcpRxDupOnlyPkts.description: Number of duplicated TCP packets received.

cftIfTcpRxDupOnlyOctets.name: cftIfTcpRxDupOnlyOctets
cftIfTcpRxDupOnlyOctets.description: Number of duplicated TCP octets received.

cftIfTcpRxDupDataPkts.name: cftIfTcpRxDupDataPkts
cftIfTcpRxDupDataPkts.description: Number of TCP packets received with duplicated data.

cftIfTcpRxDupOctetsInPartDupPkts.name: cftIfTcpRxDupOctetsInPartDupPkts
cftIfTcpRxDupOctetsInPartDupPkts.description: Number of duplicated TCP octets received in part of duplicated packets.

cftIfTcpRxDataAfterWindowPkts.name: cftIfTcpRxDataAfterWindowPkts
cftIfTcpRxDataAfterWindowPkts.description: Number of TCP packets with data received after window.

cftIfTcpRxDataAfterWindowOctets.name: cftIfTcpRxDataAfterWindowOctets
cftIfTcpRxDataAfterWindowOctets.description: Number of TCP octets with data received after window.

cftIfTcpRxPktsAfterConnClose.name: cftIfTcpRxPktsAfterConnClose
cftIfTcpRxPktsAfterConnClose.description: Number of TCP packets received after the connection close.

cftIfTcpRxWindowProbesPkts.name: cftIfTcpRxWindowProbesPkts
cftIfTcpRxWindowProbesPkts.description: Number of TCP window probing packets received.

cftIfTcpRxDupAcks.name: cftIfTcpRxDupAcks
cftIfTcpRxDupAcks.description: Number of duplicated TCP acknowledge packets received.

cftIfTcpRxAcksForUnsentData.name: cftIfTcpRxAcksForUnsentData
cftIfTcpRxAcksForUnsentData.description: Number of TCP acknowledge packets received for unsent data.

cftIfTcpRxAcksPkts.name: cftIfTcpRxAcksPkts
cftIfTcpRxAcksPkts.description: Number of TCP packets received with ACK flag on.

cftIfTcpOctetAckedByRxAcks.name: cftIfTcpOctetAckedByRxAcks
cftIfTcpOctetAckedByRxAcks.description: Number of TCP octets received with ACK flag on.

cftIfTcpRxWindowUpdatePkts.name: cftIfTcpRxWindowUpdatePkts
cftIfTcpRxWindowUpdatePkts.description: Number of TCP packets received for updating window size.

cftIfTcpSegDropByPAWS.name: cftIfTcpSegDropByPAWS
cftIfTcpSegDropByPAWS.reference: RFC 2883, An Extension to the Selective Acknowledgement (SACK) Option for TCP
cftIfTcpSegDropByPAWS.description: Number of TCP segments dropped due to Protection Against Wrapped Sequence Number (PAWS) algorithm.

cftIfTcpTxSackFackDataPkts.name: cftIfTcpTxSackFackDataPkts
cftIfTcpTxSackFackDataPkts.reference: RFC 2018, TCP Selective Acknowledgment Options RFC 2883, An Extension to the Selective Acknowledgement (SACK) Option for TCP
cftIfTcpTxSackFackDataPkts.description: Number of TCP data packets sent with SACK option on.

cftIfTcpTxSackFackDataOctets.name: cftIfTcpTxSackFackDataOctets
cftIfTcpTxSackFackDataOctets.description: Number of TCP data octets sent with SACK option on.

cftIfTcpRetxSackFackDataPkts.name: cftIfTcpRetxSackFackDataPkts
cftIfTcpRetxSackFackDataPkts.description: Number of TCP data packets re-sent with SACK option on.

cftIfTcpRetxSackFackDataOctets.name: cftIfTcpRetxSackFackDataOctets
cftIfTcpRetxSackFackDataOctets.description: Number of TCP data octets re-sent with SACK option on.

cftIfTcpSackFackConnClosed.name: cftIfTcpSackFackConnClosed
cftIfTcpSackFackConnClosed.description: Number of TCP connections closed with SACK option on.

cftIfTcpRetxSackFackTimeouts.name: cftIfTcpRetxSackFackTimeouts
cftIfTcpRetxSackFackTimeouts.description: Number of TCP timeouts re-sent with SACK option on.

cftIfTcpHdrPredictOkForAcks.name: cftIfTcpHdrPredictOkForAcks
cftIfTcpHdrPredictOkForAcks.description: Number of times the header predication code is hit by TCP packets with ACK option on.

cftIfTcpHdrPredictOkForDataPkts.name: cftIfTcpHdrPredictOkForDataPkts
cftIfTcpHdrPredictOkForDataPkts.description: Number of times the header predication code is hit by the packets of FC Data TCP connection.

cftTunnelMIBComplianceV01.name: cftTunnelMIBComplianceV01
cftTunnelMIBComplianceV01.description: A Fiber Channel tunneling implementation that lists the groups supporting configuration tunnels and statistics information of the tunnels.

cftTcpTunnelConfigGroup.name: cftTcpTunnelConfigGroup
cftTcpTunnelConfigGroup.description: The collection of objects which are used to describe and configure Fiber Channal TCP tunneling.

cftTcpTunnelStatGroup.name: cftTcpTunnelStatGroup
cftTcpTunnelStatGroup.description: The collection of objects which are used to monitor the traffic of TCP tunnels.

cftIfTcpGroup.name: cftIfTcpGroup
cftIfTcpGroup.description: The collection of objects which are used to monitor the status and statistics information of the TCP stack for the tunneled Fiber Channel interface.

cftIfTcpExtGroup.name: cftIfTcpExtGroup
cftIfTcpExtGroup.description: The collection of objects which are used to monitor the status and statistics information of the TCP stack for the tunneled Fiber Channel interface. This extension group provides more detail and specific statistics information that not all the TCP stack will support.
